        song_lyrics: "Lamplight's burning down... and my hand won't stay steady...\nBut I'm NOT finished yet— gotta get this DOWN...\nThe fire's just coals now, room's getting cold...\nI'm the last one breathing who walked those roads.\n\nI walked beside Him—\nI'm writing it down...\nSo they might believe...\nGotta get this to 'em now, so they might BELIEVE.\n\nCoin beside my hand—Caesar's face. \"Lord and God\" stamped in silver...\nEmpire's BLASPHEMY!...\nTakes me back to Thomas—\nReaching for the scars...\nMy LORD and my GOD!\nI heard him say it. I'm writing THAT down.\n\nI walked beside Him—\nI'm writing it down!\nSo they might believe...\nGotta get this to 'em NOW!\nSo they might believe!\n\nLamp's almost gone, pages in my hands...\nLast voice that walked beside Him...\nFor the scattered searching for home...\nThis witness HAS to reach them.\n\nI walked beside Him—\nI'm writing it down!\nSo they might BELIEVE!\nGotta get this to 'em NOW!\nSo they might BELIEVE!\n\nI walked beside Him—\nIt's written DOWN!\nSo they might BELIEVE!\nThis witness will reach them NOW!\nSo they might BELIEVE!\n\nLaying down my pen...\nMay they find their way home...\nHis breath won't let these words die.",
